Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1} into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g}, pepper chunks and onion to the pan.

Stir-fry until the chicken has browned all over and the veg is starting to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @Ginger Puree{15%g} to the chicken, lower the heat to medium and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Miso Paste{30%g}, @Hoisin Sauce{32%g}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g} and @Water for the Sauce{125%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then simmer gently until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything is ready, share the jasmine rice out between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon the Beijing style chicken on top.

Garnish with a sprinkle of @Black Sesame Seeds{5%g}.

Enjoy!